		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="cs">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-004_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>Dohra z <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName></p>
					<p>V tyto dny pronesl <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">americký</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">válečný</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">soud</term> v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">rozsudek</term> nad prvními čtyřiceti <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218s" type="subject">obžalovanými</term>, jak už asi víte z tisku, bylo <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">36</term> odsouzeno k <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-542" type="subject">smrti provazem</term>, zbylí <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">čtyři</term>, bezvýznamní <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">wachtposti</term></q>, dostali doživotně nebo mnoho let <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">žaláře</term>.</p>
					<p>Tento <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">rozsudek</term> má velký význam. Je jistě lepší než <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">belsenský</placeName>, ale je také mnohem lepší než
						vše, co jsme mohli očekávati od dlouhých týdnů zdlouhavého <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1129" type="subject">soudního řízení</term> v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>, kde
						nejen obžalovaní <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáci</term>, ale také jejich <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">američtí</placeName> obhájci vystupovali velmi sebevědomě, ba drze.</p>
					<p>První, co jsme my svědci z <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Československa</placeName> udělali, bylo uvědomit <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">amerického</placeName> prokurátora, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">podplukovníka</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_denson_william">Densona</persName> o tom, že se nám <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">belsenský</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">proces</term> nelíbil a že bychom neradi vystupovali v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">procesu</term> podobném. Uvedli jsme příklad, kdy se
							<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">belsenský</placeName> obhájce neštítil pošpinit památku našich mrtvých kamarádů jen proto, aby pomohl svým <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject"
							>nacistickým klientům</term>. Prohlásili jsme, že opustíme ihned sál a nezúčastníme se dalšího líčení, kdyby se něco podobného mělo udat také v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>. Ujistili nás, že udělají
						vše, aby se <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">americký</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">proces</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">dachovský</placeName> nepodobal v ničem <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">britskému</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">procesu</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">belsenskému</placeName> - a že se jim to snad opravdu povedlo, dokazuje přísný a spravedlivý <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">rozsudek</term>.
						Ač zde mělo jistě vliv i světové veřejné mínění, které bylo <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">belsenským</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">rozsudkem</term> pobouřeno.</p>
					<p>Řekl jsem, že tento <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">rozsudek</term> nás překvapil a myslím, že je nutno vysvětlit, proč jsme <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">procesu</term> ze
						začátku tak málo důvěřovali. První věc, která nás <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">české</placeName> svědky mrzela, byla určitá pravidla, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">soudem</term>
						předem stanovená. Tak smělo být mluveno a žalováno jen o skutcích, provedených přímo v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> nebo v jeho <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567"
							type="subject">filiálních táborech</term> /<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-224" type="camp">Kaufering</placeName> atd./ <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">Essesák</term>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001263">Moll</persName>, který byl známým <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">vrahem</term> tisíců <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-510" type="subject">vězňů</term> v <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Osvěčimi</placeName>, odkud po <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623"
							type="subject">evakuaci</term> na začátku tohoto roku přišel pouze na 5 neděl do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>, směl být obžalován jen za skutky, provedené za těchto 5 neděl. <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Osvěčimské</placeName> minulosti se nikdo nesměl dotknout ani slovem.</p>
					<p>Jiná taková omezení: před <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">soudem</term> rozhodovaly jen delikty spáchané po <date when="1942-01-01">1. 1. 1942</date>. Dokazoval - li na příklad <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesák</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_jarolin_josef">Jarolim</persName>, že se <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zastřelení</term> tisíců <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">Rusů</term> sice
						zúčastnil, ale že to bylo na podzim <date when="1941">1941</date>, doufal, že bude osvobozen.</p>
					<p>Všechna tato omezení vedla k groteskním výstupům, neboť obhajoba /čtyři <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">američtí důstojníci</term> a jeden <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-431"
							type="subject">německý</term> advokát/ nevynechali jedinou příležitost, aby svým klientům touto cestou napomáhali. Tak došlo na příklad hned při výpovědi prvního svědka k diskusi <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6255148/europe.html">Evropanovi</placeName>
						nepochopitelné. Po obsazení <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">tábora</term>
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> /<date when="1945-04-29">29. dubna 1945</date>/ byl sem oficiálně vyslán <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">plukovník</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_chavez_david">Chavez</persName>, aby zjistil <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">válečné</term> zločiny, spáchané <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-431"
							type="subject">Němci</term>. Když však tento <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">americký</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">důstojník</term> chtěl zahájit <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">proces</term> vylíčením situace, kterou v <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> nalezl <date when="1945-04-30">30. dubna 1945</date>, byl okamžitě přerušen obhájci, kteří tvrdili, že <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127"
							type="subject">soud</term> se nehodlá zabývat poměry v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">táboře</term> po <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">osvobození</term> a že tudíž výpověď
						vyšetřujícího <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">důstojníka</term> je zbytečná. Teprve po další šarvátce, když bylo zjištěno, že <persName ref="#ehri_dc_chavez_david">Chavez</persName> chce mluvit o <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">vězních</term>, kteří sice <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">umřeli</term> po <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573"
							type="subject">osvobození</term>, ale na následky křivd spáchaných na nich <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáky</term> před <date when="1945-04-29">29. dubnem</date>, bylo mu dovoleno vypovídat.</p>
					<p>Dále byly za trestné považovány pouze delikty spáchané na občanech států tehdy s <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Německem</placeName> válčících. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject"
							>Lagršéfarct</term> dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_hintermayer_fritz">Hintermayer</persName> tedy nezapíral, že <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">zabíjel</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-320" type="subject">nervově choré vězně</term> injekcemi, ale tvrdil, že šlo výhradně o <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">heftlinky</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-431" type="subject">německé</term>, tedy o věc, nenamířenou proti nepřátelům <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Říše</term>. Tato groteskní teorie šla
						tak da-</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-004_02.jpg" n="2"/>
					<p>leko, že když náš <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">český</placeName> svědek dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_blaha_frantisek">Bláha</persName> mluvil o oblibě, které se u některých <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-495" type="subject">experimentujících</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáckých</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">lékařů</term> těšili zvláště <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-670" type="subject">cikáni</term>, povstal <placeName
							ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">americký</placeName> obhájce, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">podplukovník</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_bates_douglas">Bates</persName>, a prohlásil, že <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-670" type="subject">cikáni</term> nebyli ve <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">válce</term> s
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Německem</placeName> a že tudíž celá věc nemá pro <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">proces</term> význam. Sklidili za to ovšem jen smích.
						Stejně se pokoušeli znehodnotit i naše svědectví, protože ani my jsme neválčili.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">Rozsudek</term> ovšem dokazuje, jak málo měnila všechna tato omezení spravedlivý názor soudců. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001263">Moll</persName>,
							<persName ref="#ehri_dc_jarolin_josef">Jarolim</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_hintermayer_fritz">Hintermayer</persName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-542" type="subject">visí</term> právě tak bezpečně jako <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">komandant</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_weiss_martin">Weiss</persName>, který toho tolik napovídal o tom, co všechno udělal ve prospěch <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">vězňů</term>, že se ho veřejný žalobce nakonec ironicky zeptal, jestli
						tedy tvrdí, že <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> bylo sanatorium. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_weiss_martin">Weiss</persName> se hrdě vzpřímil a prohlásil: <q><placeName
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> war ein gutes <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">Lager</term>!</q> /<placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> byl dobrý <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">tábor</term>!/</p>
					<p>Veliký politický význam tohoto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">procesu</term> neleží ovšem ve vlastním přelíčení, často až nesnesitelně zkresleném snahou obhájců a jejich svědků. Je v konečném postoji <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1128" type="subject">soudců</term> k celému problému. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">Rozsudek</term> dal totiž plně za pravdu veřejnému žalobci, který neustále
						opakoval, že tito <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">obžalovaní</term> nemají býti vůbec souzeni za to, co jednotlivě a na vlastní zodpovědnost napáchali na vězních, nýbrž že musejí být <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">odsouzeni</term> k <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">smrti</term> už jedině proto, že náleží k organizaci, jejímž hlavním úkolem bylo <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">vraždit</term> a týrat politické odpůrce a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">válečné zajatce</term>.</p>
					<p>Tato teorie zvítězila. Bude - li tedy <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">dachovský</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">proces</term> považován za závazný příklad, <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">český</placeName> hrdelný trest každého <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Němce</placeName>, ať <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">esesáka</term> nebo <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485"
							type="subject">kápa</term>, o kterém se prokáže, že byl zapojen jakýmkoli způsobem do mašinérie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">koncentračních táborů</term>. Bylo to jistě ne v poslední řadě i vystoupení <placeName
							ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">českých</placeName> svědků, které přimělo <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">soud</term> k tak významnému <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">rozhodnutí</term>.</p>
					<p>Za <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">dokumentační akci</term> přijal:</p>
					<p>Za archiv přijal:</p>
					<p>Opis: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_bondy_ruth">R. Bramerová</persName></p>
					<p><placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Praha</placeName>, <date when="1946-02-01">1. II. 1946</date></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-004_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p><placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> Epilogue</p>
					<p>In the past several days, the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">U.S.</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">War</term> Crimes <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">Tribunal</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177"
							type="camp">Dachau</placeName> has <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">sentenced</term> the first forty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">defendants</term>. As you’ve likely
						already read in the papers, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">36</term> people were sentenced to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-542" type="subject">death by hanging</term>. The other <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">four</term>, insignificant <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject">wachtposts</term>,</q> received life sentences or long <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> sentences.</p>
					<p>This is a very important <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">verdict</term>. It’s even better than the one from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen</placeName>, but it’s also
						much more than we could have expected from the weeks-long <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1129" type="subject">trial</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>, where the
						accused <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> acted in a confident and sometimes rude manner, just like their <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">American</placeName> defense
						attorneys.</p>
					<p>The first thing that we, the witnesses from <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovakia</placeName>, did was to tell the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">American</placeName> prosecutor, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">lieutenant colonel</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_denson_william">Denson</persName>, that we were very dissatisfied with the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term> and that we wouldn’t like to take part in a similar <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term>. We told him how the defense
						attorney in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen</placeName> did not hesitate to tarnish the memory of our dead friends in order to help his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218" type="subject"
							>Nazi clients</term>. We declared that we would immediately leave the courtroom and wouldn’t participate in any other trial if something similar were to take place in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>.
						He assured us that they would do everything in their power to make sure that the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">U.S.</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> wouldn’t resemble the <placeName
							ref="https://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">British</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen</placeName>. The strict and just <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">verdict</term> proves that they succeeded. The world’s outrage at the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">verdict</term> also had a significant impact.</p>
					<p>I have said that this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">verdict</term> surprised us and I think we must explain why we didn’t trust this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject"
							>trial</term> very much at the beginning. The first thing that we <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> witnesses were dismayed at were certain rules established by the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">court</term> prior to the trial. We were only allowed to speak about and press charges against acts committed in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177"
							type="camp">Dachau</placeName> or its <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">affiliated camps</term> (<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-224" type="camp">Kaufering</placeName> etc.). <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS member</term>
						<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001263">Moll</persName> was the notorious <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murderer</term> of thousands of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-510" type="subject">prisoners</term> in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>. After it was <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuated</term> at the beginning of this year, he spent a mere five weeks in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>. He could only
						be prosecuted for the acts he committed during these 5 weeks. Nobody was allowed to utter a single word about his past in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Other similar limitations: before the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">trial</term>, only offenses committed after <date when="1942-01-01">1.1.1942</date> mattered. If <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_jarolin_josef">Jarolim</persName> proved, for instance, that he participated in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shooting</term> of thousands of <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">Russians</term>, but that it occured in the fall of <date when="1941">1941</date>, he had reason to hope that he would be freed.</p>
					<p>All of these limitations led to grotesque pronouncements, for the defense (four <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">American officers</term> and one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-431"
							type="subject">German</term> attorney) didn’t miss a single opportunity to help their clients in this way. And so, for example, right after the first witness’s testimony, a discussion took place that a <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6255148/europe.html"
							>European</placeName> would find inconceivable. After the occupation of the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">concentration camp</term> (<date when="1945-04-29">April 29th, 1945</date>), <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">colonel</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_chavez_david">Chavez</persName> officially sent me to uncover <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">war</term> crimes committed by <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-431" type="subject">Germans</term>. But when this <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">American</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">officer</term> wanted to open the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term> by describing the situation that he discovered in <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> on <date when="1945-04-30">April 30th, 1945</date>, he was immediately interrupted by the defense, who claimed that the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject">court</term> was not supposed to concern itself with the conditions in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> after it was <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberated</term>, and so therefore the statement of the investigating <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">officer</term> was irrelevant. Only after
						more arguments, during which it was discovered that <persName ref="#ehri_dc_chavez_david">Chavez</persName> wanted to speak about the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">prisoners</term> who <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> after <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term>, but as a consequence of injustices committed against them by <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS members</term> prior to <date when="1945-04-29">April 29th</date>, he was allowed to continue his testimony.</p>
					<p>Furthermore, only crimes committed against citizens of the nations at war with <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> were considered criminal offenses. The <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">camp's head doctor</term>, Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_hintermayer_fritz">Hintermayer</persName>, didn’t deny that he <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532"
							type="subject">killed</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-320" type="subject">mentally ill prisoners</term> with lethal injections, but claimed that they were all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-431" type="subject"
							>German</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">prisoners</term>, and that therefore it was not aimed at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Reich</term>’s enemies. This grotesque theory was
						taken to such extremes</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-004_02.jpg" n="2"/>
					<p>that when our <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> witness, Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_blaha_frantisek">Bláha</persName>, spoke about how certain <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216"
							type="subject">SS</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-477" type="subject">doctors</term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-495" type="subject">who carried out experiments</term> looked forward especially to experimenting on <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-670" type="subject">Roma</term> prisoners, the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/6252001/united-states.html">American</placeName> defense attorney, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">lieutenant colonel</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_bates_douglas">Bates</persName>, stood up and said that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-670" type="subject">Roma</term> weren’t at <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject"
							>war</term> with <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> and so therefore this statement should be considered irrelevant for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130"
							type="subject">trial</term>. But this only won him laughter from those present in court. Yet he still tried to invalidate our testimony, because we, too, hadn’t waged war.</p>
					<p>However, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">verdict</term> proves just how little these limitations influenced the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1128" type="subject">judges</term>’ sense of
						justice. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001263">Moll</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_jarolin_josef">Jarolim</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_hintermayer_fritz">Hintermayer</persName> were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-542" type="subject">hanged</term> just as surely as <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">commandant</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_weiss_martin">Weiss</persName>, who spoke at length about all the things he did to help the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">prisoners</term>, leading the prosecutor to ironically ask him if he truly
						meant to claim that <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> was a sanatorium. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_weiss_martin">Weiss</persName> drew himself up proudly and stated: <q><placeName
								ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> war ein gutes <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">Lager</term>!</q> (<placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName> was a good <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>!)</p>
					<p>The great political significance of this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term> lies not in the proceedings themselves, which were often tarnished by the intolerable efforts of the defense and its witnesses, but in the
						judges’ final approach to the problem. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">verdict</term> vindicated the prosecutor, who constantly repeated that these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1218"
							type="subject">defendants</term> should not be tried for the crimes they individually decided to commit against the prisoners, but should be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">sentenced</term> to <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> simply because they belonged to an organization whose main goal was to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">murder</term> and torture
						political opponents and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-511" type="subject">prisoners of war</term>.</p>
					<p>This theory won out in the end. If the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1130" type="subject">trial</term> will turn out to be any kind of precedent, it will be that of the ultimate <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> punishment for
						every <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">German</placeName>, whether an <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS member</term> or <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485" type="subject">capo</term>, who is found to have been connected in any way to the running of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>. And
						last but certainly not least, the testimony of the <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> witnesses was one of the main reasons that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1127" type="subject"
							>court</term> made such a significant <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1131" type="subject">ruling</term>.</p>
					<p>On behalf of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-657" type="subject">Documentation Campaign</term>:</p>
					<p>On behalf of the archive:</p>
					<p>Transcript: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_bondy_ruth">R. Bramerová</persName></p>
